Set of terms is written as $$\tau (\Sigma, V)$$, $$\tau(\Sigma)$$ shorthand

Every term that does not contain variables is closed (or ground)

We have a substitution to map variables to terms:
$$\overline\tau(a(x,y)) = a(\overline\tau(x), \overline\tau(y)) = a(s(0), m(0,0))$$

Therefore, every variable, constant and result is a term